  "text": "Located four key files implementing the Android Activity lifecycle in the aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base repository:\n\n1. **Activity.java** (core/java/android/app/Activity.java): Defines the base `Activity` class (extends `ContextThemeWrapper`) that provides the framework for Android activities. This class contains the lifecycle callback methods including `onCreate()`, `onStart()`, `onResume()`, `onPause()`, `onStop()`, and `onDestroy()` that developers override to handle activity lifecycle events.\n\n2. **ActivityThread.java** (core/java/android/app/ActivityThread.java): Implements the `ActivityThread` class (extends `ClientTransactionHandler` and implements `ActivityThreadInternal`) which is the main thread of an Android application. It manages the execution of activities, services, and other components in the application process, and is responsible for driving lifecycle transitions and executing lifecycle callbacks on activities.\n\n3. **ActivityRecord.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java): Defines the server-side `ActivityRecord` class (extends `WindowToken`) that represents an activity on the system server. This class tracks the state of activities from the system server perspective and coordinates with the window manager for rendering and display.\n\n4. **ActivityTaskManagerService.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java): Implements the system service `ActivityTaskManagerService` (extends `IActivityTaskManager.Stub`) that manages activity stacks, tasks, and the overall lifecycle coordination across the system. This service is responsible for starting activities, managing back stacks, and enforcing system-wide activity management policies."
}

